EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 182300 UTC
ON THURSDAY A LARGE AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WITH VARIOUS
CENTRES LIES TO THE SW OF ICELAND. OVERNIGHT THESE LOW
CENTRES ARE EXP TO COMBINE TO FORM A DEEP LOW PRESSURE
CENTRE 977 ACROSS ROCKALL BY MIDDAY ON FRIDAY. THIS LOW
IS THEN LIKELY TO MOV E ACROSS SCOTLAND THROUGH FRIDAY IN
TO THE NERN N SEA. BY MIDDAY ON SATURDAY THE LOW IS EXP
TO LIE OVER THE S OF SCANDINAVIA AND A NEW LOW CENTRE
SHOULD DEVELOP ACROSS FAEROES. THIS LOW IS LIKELY TO MOV
SLWY E TOWARDS SHETLAND FOR SUNDAY. ON THURSDAY AND
FRIDAY NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS THE NE OF
CULLERCOATS. ON FRIDAY NIGHT WINDS MAY STRENGTHEN TO GALE
FOR AT TIME ACROSS THE FAR NE AS STRG OR NEAR GALE FORCE
WINDS SPREAD IN FM THE SW TO AFFECT THE MAJORITY OF
CULLERCOATS ON SATURDAY. WINDS GRADUALLY EASING OVERNIGHT
BUT FURTHER STRG WINDS ARE EXP TO DEVELOP IN THE S ON
SUNDAY.
